This paper is about structured weight pruning for deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with techniques for improving the efficiency of DNNs. Additionally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also possible sub-categories, as the paper discusses methods for accelerating DNNs on GPUs.
